	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=48553><span id= >Lawman</span></a><br><span id=notbold>19 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I'd just like to clear a couple of things up on the effects of the Defender...First, it's 150DD combined with a stun, that may or may not have an actual duration...it's enough to say that the stun will last for so short a time you won't notice it probably and might as well be called a zero duration stun. The stun only serves to interupt casting and is unresistable. It is unfortunate that the stun and the DD are a proc, so the stun is basically usless unless it happens to go off when your opponet is casting...Second, there isn't any DOT associated with it..that was a bug that was fixed many months ago. The bug allowed the DD to became a DOT after the first couple of seconds and its duration was basically infinite. Allowing paladins to kill everything in a single blow...given they had the time to stick around and watch it die. That is no more though and it now works like it was intended...Third and last, though its not posted on the weapons stats, you can bash with it...yes...bash...even though its a 2hs wep and you don't have a shield. All in all, I would consider the weapon to be "fair" when compaired to other epics...but when put in the hands of a paladin of a high 50s lvl...well...its the cherry on top of the sunday. The stats and saves it gives are nothing to sneeze at and the AC is nice...damage is good but not great...but the proc leaves you wanting more...heh...thats just like that cherry though...always looking for another...Ok, that's my two copper. Later all, be safe and good hunting</p>&nbsp;<br>Lawman<br>65th Paladin of Marr<br>Valoran<br>Karana</td></td></tr>
